{% # Font Preload v1.0.1 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.0.1 — suppress AssetPreload theme-check: `preload_tag` needs an asset_url-family input and emits no `crossorigin`, but this font URL is metaobject-hosted and fonts require `crossorigin` to avoid a double fetch — the manual link is correct here
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description
  Preloads the base typeface's first woff2 so the browser starts the font fetch before the inlined @font-face block parses, cutting the FOUT swap delay. Emits nothing when no base typeface / woff2 is configured. `crossorigin` matches the @font-face fetch (Shopify's font CDN serves with CORS) so there's no double download, and the URL is the same `asset.url` that `utility--font-face` emits.

  Depends on: `settings.base_text_style` → `typeface` → `font` → `asset_list` (see `utility--font-face`).

  @example {% render 'utility--font-preload' %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign base_typeface = settings.base_text_style.font_family.value
  assign preload_url = ''

  for font in base_typeface.font_list.value
    if font.asset_list.value.size == 0
      continue
    endif
    for asset in font.asset_list.value
      assign asset_ext = asset.url | split: '.' | last | split: '?' | first
      if asset_ext == 'woff2'
        assign preload_url = asset.url
        break
      endif
    endfor
    if preload_url != blank
      break
    endif
  endfor

  if preload_url == blank
    break
  endif
%}
{% comment %} theme-check-disable AssetPreload {% endcomment %}
<link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" href="{{ preload_url }}" crossorigin>
{% comment %} theme-check-enable AssetPreload {% endcomment %}
